      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a pretty strong take. You called it a \"victory\" and said the coal infrastructure is \"outdated and inefficient.\" Is that actually what most people in the state think, or is that just one perspective? What are people on the other side saying about the actual economic impact on coal towns?",
