    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean \"long-term benefits are undeniable\" is a big claim. if the transition is causing local economic collapses and people are losing their livelihoods right now, isn't it kind of unfair to frame it as \"undeniable\" when the cost is being paid by specific groups of people? it feels like the bill is prioritizing a specific environmental agenda over the actual survival of these communities.",
